Like God, we're just being honest and it can make some of us anxious.

36:00.202 --> 36:07.634
And as we look to steward it, whether we feel like we have a lot of it or we feel like we're really struggling, as we look to steward it, we know

36:07.906 --> 36:30.609
that at the end of the day, the answer is still to bring it all to you because it comes from you in order that we might direct it with intentionality, that we might steward it well, that we might make wise decisions so that we can point more people to you with our lives and with our generosity.

36:33.071 --> 36:35.954
And God, I admit, we admit there are times

36:36.514 --> 36:50.636
We confess where emotionally we get up, we get caught up in a longing for more, a desire to be in control, and a mindset that what we have is just never enough.

36:53.280 --> 37:04.978
And God, we know what that does is it just diminishes what you did on the cross, for what you did on the cross was enough for us, no matter where we're at financially.

37:06.466 --> 37:07.688
And God, we come to you.

37:07.828 --> 37:17.643
I pray for each and every person here who's gonna have a kitchen table conversation, who's gonna take a hard look at a spreadsheet, who's gonna sit down and actually look at where their finances are going.

37:17.663 --> 37:20.567
Who's gonna work on a plan, who's gonna be at the financial learning experience.

37:21.008 --> 37:24.393
God, I know the anxiety and the emotion in the midst of that.

37:25.074 --> 37:28.839
And I just pray that David know you walking alongside of them.

37:30.582 --> 37:36.050
And that we wouldn't just see the open door here and look at it, but we would have the courage to walk through it.

37:37.602 --> 37:38.611
and I pray this in your name.

